The new aircraft boasts millions of ambient anti-jet lag LED lights, hospital-grade air filters, and the lowest cabin altitude in an airplane on the market, the Daily Mail reports. Cabin altitude is what scientists identify as attributing to jet lag symptoms – feeling of fatigue and shortness of breath – at 6,500 feet. The A35-1000 maintains an altitude of only 6,000 feet. context_meta.title: Crashes kill three in Hollister-Gilroy area
context_meta.summary: GILROY — The California Highway Patrol is urging motorists to be more careful behind the wheel after three people, including a 6-year-old boy, died in separate crashes in the Hollister-Gilroy area over the weekend. The first collision occurred on State Route 152 east of Lake Road in Gilroy at 2:10 p.m. Saturday when the driver of a 2014 Ford veered off the roadway and hit a tree, according to the CHP. The driver, described as a 49-year-old Monterey woman, died at the scene. Her 49-year-old passenger was airlifted to Regional Medical Center in San Jose with minor injuries.
